EXPLORE
  Move civilians out of a sector to claim new territory.

SYNTAX
  explore <x,y> <path> <commodity> <amount>
  expl    <x,y> <path> <commodity> <amount>

DESCRIPTION
  Sends civilians (or other commodities) along a path to claim
  adjacent unowned sectors.  Any unowned sector a civilian enters
  becomes yours.  The civilian is left in the last sector reached.

  <x,y>       - starting sector (must be yours)
  <path>       - string of direction letters (e.g. "jjn")
  <commodity>  - commodity to carry, usually 'c' for civilians
  <amount>     - how many to move

  Direction letters:
    u  upper-right      j  right
    n  lower-right      b  lower-left
    g  left             y  upper-left
    h  stop (halt)      v  view (look without moving)

  Each step costs mobility (see info btu).  You cannot move through
  sea, mountain, or enemy-owned sectors.

  Exploring consumes food in the destination sector if the civilians
  stay there — make sure there's food or they will starve.

EXAMPLE
  explore 0,0 jj civ 10    move 10 civs right-right from capital
  explore 4,2 n civ 5      send 5 civs lower-right from 4,2
  explore 2,-2 jjj civ 1   scout three sectors east

